Create a defined addressable for the given content.

The Content is assumed to be non-writable, and will be copied when mutations are required.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/jitlink/jitlink-h/#l00179">179</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/jitlink/jitlink-h">JITLink.h</a>.

### Block() {#a5b0d662cdfa584aced6dc40d5c4eb2d9}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>llvm::jitlink::Block::Block (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/section">Section</a> &amp; Parent, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mutablearrayref">MutableArrayRef</a>&lt; char &gt; Content, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executoraddr">orc::ExecutorAddr</a> Address, uint64&#95;t Alignment, uint64&#95;t AlignmentOffset)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Create a defined addressable for the given content.

The content is assumed to be writable, and the caller is responsible for ensuring that it lives for the duration of the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/block">Block</a>&#39;s lifetime. The standard way to achieve this is to allocate it on the Graph&#39;s allocator.

### isContentMutable() {#a42992393f27fa4c28ce4204f8bf7caaa}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="bool llvm::jitlink::Block::isContentMutable () const"
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Returns true if this block&#39;s content is mutable.

This is primarily useful for asserting that a block is already in a mutable state prior to modifying the content. E.g. when applying fixups we expect the block to already be mutable as it should have been copied to working memory.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/jitlink/jitlink-h/#l00296">296</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/jitlink/jitlink-h">JITLink.h</a>.

Returns true if this is a zero-fill block.

If true, getSize is callable but getContent is not (the content is defined to be a sequence of zero bytes of length Size).
